ans, functionals $F(w,\\nabla w)$\nof a vector potential $w$ and its gradient, that act as null-Lagrangians when\n$\\nabla w$ is constrained for $x\\in\\Omega$ to take values in certain sets $\\cal\nA$, of appropriate non-linear manifolds, and when $w$ satisfies appropriate\nboundary conditions. The extension to certain non-linear minimization problems\nis also sketched.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 10 Dec 2017 22:05:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 15 Feb 2018 15:16:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 22 Feb 2018 00:26:35 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 3 Mar 2018 22:58:26 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 18 Jun 2018 23:31:58 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 15 Nov 2018 18:42:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-16"}
