ctron\nspectral indices $p^{\\rm CI}$, etc.) using color indices. Overall, we conclude\nthat $\\sim$ 90\\% of colors are constant in time and can be accounted for by the\nsimplest external forward shock model, while the varying color indices call for\nmore detailed modeling.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Dec 2017 10:23:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 25 Feb 2018 17:52:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 12 Dec 2018 17:35:53 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 13 Dec 2018 16:58:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-14"}
